.pre-commit-config.yaml.message:
Is this only block files with merge conflict markers in them? I hope it does not try to figure out if my patch is in merge conflict with the HEAD of the target branch as sometimes I need to push update to reviews that are in merge conflict   solving the merge in a later patch set.

// later OK it is just the former. which is good.
https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks/blob/master/pre_commit_hooks/check_merge_conflict.py

What I'm objecting to is automatically fixing it. It's more likely that authors will be editing existing files, rather than creating entirely new ones. As such, consider if the author had done something like this:

    def test(x):
        if x:
    \tprint(x)

That might look okay in their editor, because tabs were 8 spaces. However, the plugin assumes tabs = a fixed number of spaces so fixing things would result in incorrect syntax:

    def test(x):
        if x:
        print(x)

I'd rather not attempt to guess this and simply rely on flake8 catching these issues for us.

